\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 auch ein beliebiges Skalarfeld einsetzen.) Bei konstantem
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 erhält man 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
ad_{-f}v(x)=\left(\begin{array}{c}
1\\
-A_{1}-\sigma A_{2}\sin(x_{1})\\
0\end{array}\right).\label{eq:pocf-synchron-ad-v}\end{equation}

\end_inset

Ergänzt man diese zwei Vektorfelder um ein weiteres Vektorfeld 
\begin_inset Formula $w(x)=\tfrac{\partial}{\partial x_{3}}$
\end_inset

, dann erhält man drei linear unabhängige Vektorfelder, deren Lie-Klammern
 identisch verschwinden.
 Damit sind die Voraussetzungen des Begradigungssatzes
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "thm:simultane-begradigung-von-VF"

\end_inset

 erfüllt und die gewünschte Koordinatentransformation kann über die Flußverkettu
ng 
\begin_inset Formula \[
x=S(z)=\varphi_{z_{1}}^{v}\circ\varphi_{z_{2}}^{ad_{-f}v}\circ\varphi_{z_{3}}^{w}(p)\]

\end_inset

berechnet werden.
 Für 
\begin_inset Formula $p=0$
\end_inset

 erhält man 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\begin{array}{rcl}
x_{1} & = & z_{2}\\
x_{2} & = & z_{1}-A_{1}z_{2}+\sigma A_{2}(\cos(z_{2})-1)\\
x_{3} & = & z_{3}+\sigma(z_{1}-D_{1}z_{2}).\end{array}\label{eq:pocf-synchron-S}\end{equation}

\end_inset

Diese Koordinatentransformation überführt das System
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:synchronmotor"

\end_inset

 in die gewünschte partielle Beobachter-Normalform 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\left(\begin{array}{c}
\dot{z}_{1}\\
\dot{z}_{2}\\
\dot{z}_{3}\end{array}\right)=\left(\begin{array}{cc|c}
0 & 0 & 0\\
1 & 0 & 0\\
\hline 0 & 0 & 0\end{array}\right)\left(\begin{array}{c}
z_{1}\\
z_{2}\\
z_{3}\end{array}\right)+\underbrace{\left(\begin{array}{c}
\alpha_{10}+\alpha_{11}\sigma+\alpha_{12}\sigma^{2}\\
\alpha_{20}+\alpha_{21}\sigma\\
\alpha_{30}+\alpha_{31}\sigma+\alpha_{32}\sigma^{2}+\alpha_{33}\sigma^{3}\end{array}\right)}_{{\displaystyle \alpha(z_{2},z_{3},u)}},\quad y=z_{2}\]

\end_inset

mit 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\begin{array}{lcl}
\alpha_{10} & = & B_{1}-(A_{2}z_{3}+B_{2}\cos(z_{2}))\sin(z_{2})\\
\alpha_{11} & = & A_{2}(D_{1}-A_{1})z_{2}\sin(z_{2})\\
\alpha_{12} & = & A_{2}^{2}(\cos(z_{2})-1)\sin(z_{2})\\
\alpha_{20} & = & z_{1}-A_{1}z_{2}\\
\alpha_{21} & = & A_{2}(\cos(z_{2})-1)\\
\alpha_{30} & = & -D_{1}z_{3}+D_{2}\cos(z_{2})\\
\alpha_{31} & = & -B_{1}+D_{1}(D_{1}-A_{1})z_{2}+(A_{2}z_{3}+B_{2}\cos(z_{2}))\sin(z_{2})\\
\alpha_{32} & = & A_{2}(D_{1}(\cos(z_{2})-1)+(A_{1}-D_{1})z_{2}\sin(z_{2}))\\
\alpha_{33} & = & A_{2}^{2}(\cos(z_{2})-1)\sin(z_{2}).\end{array}\]

\end_inset

